For the steaks, heat a large griddle pan until hot. Rub the oil into the steaks, season with salt and pepper and cook for 3â€“4 minutes on each side, depending on the size of the steaks and your preference. Leave the steaks to rest for 5 minutes.For the salad, add the lemon juice to 250ml/9fl oz water and soak the artichoke slices.Place the artichokes, fennel, radicchio and rocket into a large salad bowl.Mix together the oil and vinegar in a small bowl.Season the steaks with sea salt and pepper again and slice. Dress the salad and serve alongside the steak slices.